 Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, originally a short form of compound names such as   Ermintrude   containing the word <i>erm(en)</i>, <i>irm(en)</i> ‘entire’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, but its popularity in medieval England was greatly enhanced by the fact that it had been borne by the mother of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Emma Grainsby was born in 1190, in Grainsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William de Grainsby, was 20 and her mother, Mrs William de Grainsby, was 18. She had at least 1 son with William de Welles. She died on 30 September 1226, in Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1190–30 September 1226":"1190–30. september 1226","1190–1226":"1190–1226","1187–1241":"1187–1241","1226–1265":"1226–1265","1170–1226":"1170–1226","1172–Female":"1172–Surnud","1190":"1190","1226":"1226","1265":"1265","1187":"1187","Abt 1226":"umbes 1226","1241":"1241","1172":"1172","30 September 1226":"30. september 1226","1170":"1170","Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Spilsby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Grainsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Grainsby, Lincolnshire, England","Welles Manor, Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Spilsby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1190–30 September 1226":"1190–30. syyskuuta 1226","1190–1226":"1190–1226","1187–1241":"1187–1241","1226–1265":"1226–1265","1170–1226":"1170–1226","1172–Female":"1172–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1226":"1226","1265":"1265","1187":"1187","Abt 1226":"noin 1226","1241":"1241","1172":"1172","30 September 1226":"30. syyskuuta 1226","1170":"1170","Spilsby, Lincolnshire, England":"Spilsby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Grai